The paper deals with the problem of jointly clustering and learning representations, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of deep learning techniques and the focus on $k$-Means clustering suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The mention of datasets and objects also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
